# My Art Gallery

## Project Overview

My Art Gallery is a web application designed to showcase artwork. It allows users to add, edit, and view various pieces of art. The application consists of a frontend built with **React** and a backend powered by **NestJS**.

### Features

#### Frontend (React)
- User-friendly interface for adding and displaying artworks.
- Form to submit new artwork including title, description, image, client link, and publication status.
- Responsive design for both desktop and mobile views.
- Validation for required fields.

#### Backend (NestJS)
- RESTful API to handle CRUD operations for artworks.
- Middleware for error handling and data validation.
- Supports TypeScript for enhanced developer experience.

## Instructions to Run the Application

### Prerequisites
- Ensure you have [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) installed.

## Getting Started

To run the application locally, first clone the repository from GitHub using `git clone https://github.com/BucataruIoan1/MyArtGallery.git`. Navigate into the project folder with `cd MyArtGallery`. Then, to run the backend, navigate to the backend directory with `cd myartgallery-backend`, install the dependencies with `npm install`, and start the server using `npm run start`. Next, open a new terminal, navigate to the frontend directory with `cd myartgallery-frontend`, install the dependencies with `npm install`, and start the frontend application using `npm start`. Finally, access the application in your web browser at `http://localhost:3001`.

## Run the Backend (NestJS)

cd myartgallery-backend
npm install
npm run start

## Run the Frontend (React)

cd myartgallery-frontend
npm install
npm start
